Follow the instructions below to create a Virtual Machine Scale Set with autoscaling configuration.
	1. Subscription: Select your respective subscription.
	2. Resource Group: Use your assigned resource group.
	3. Virtual Machine Scale Set Configuration:
		‚óã Name: yourname-vmss001
		‚óã Region: East US
		‚óã Operating System: Windows Server 2019
		‚óã Security Type: Standard
		‚óã Authentication Type: Password
		‚óã Username: tapout
		‚óã Password: Sunday@Aug@2025
		‚óã VM Size: B1s or B1ms
		‚óã Availability Zone: Select Zone Redundant (distribute instances across 2 zones)
	4. Storage: Keep default settings.
	5. Networking:
		‚óã Virtual Network: Use the assigned VNet/Subnet
		‚óã Load Balancer: None
		‚óã Inbound Ports Allowed: 80, 443, 3389
	6. Scaling Configuration:
		‚óã Default instance count: 2
		‚óã Instance limits:
			¬ß Minimum = 1
			¬ß Maximum = 6
		‚óã Scale Out Rule: If average CPU > 80%, add 2 instance
		‚óã Scale In Rule: If average CPU < 20%, remove 1 instance
	7. Monitoring: Disable.
	8. Advanced Settings:
		‚óã Enable Auto Shutdown: Yes, set to 6 PM IST (without notification)
		‚óã Startup script: (provide if required, otherwise skip)
