Task#12: Create a Virtual Machine using PowerShell
Creating a VM using PowerShell in Azure Portal- 
Create a VM    use your own resource group etc        

In the below script 
replace myResourceGroup with your resource group name
replace myVM with your Virtual Machine name
Location - Use any
replace myVnet with your Virtual Network name (Similar to VM name)
  
      
New-AzVm `
  -ResourceGroupName 'myResourceGroup' `
  -Name 'myVM' `
  -Location 'East US' `
  -VirtualNetworkName 'myVnet' `
  -SubnetName 'mySubnet' `
  -SecurityGroupName 'myNetworkSecurityGroup' `
  -PublicIpAddressName 'myPublicIpAddress' `
  -OpenPorts 80,3389 `
  -Size 'Standard_B1s'



Using Windows PS windows- 


Check version -                 $PSVersionTable  (should be 5 above)

Install Azure module-      Install-Module AzureAD
				  Install-Module -Name Az -AllowClobber -Scope allusers
				
Set remote execution-    Set-ExecutionPolicy -Executionpolicy RemoteSigned -Force

Connect to MS Azure-     Connect-AzAccount or az login


